# Upscan demo landing page
upscan.demo.title = Upscan proof of concept
upscan.demo.heading = Upscan proof of concept
upscan.demo.intro = This demonstrates two ways of using HMRC's Upscan service to upload files from a frontend service.

upscan.demo.userUpload.heading = Use case 1: User file upload
upscan.demo.userUpload.description = The user selects a file on a GOV.UK page and it is uploaded directly from their browser to Upscan (S3) for virus scanning and storage.
upscan.demo.userUpload.button = Try user file upload

upscan.demo.serviceGenerated.heading = Use case 2: Service-generated file upload
upscan.demo.serviceGenerated.description = The user fills in a form, and the service generates a file from that data, then uploads it to Upscan on the server side.
upscan.demo.serviceGenerated.button = Try service-generated upload

upscan.demo.howItWorks.heading = How Upscan works
upscan.demo.howItWorks.step1 = The frontend service calls upscan-initiate to request a pre-signed upload URL and form fields.
upscan.demo.howItWorks.step2 = Upscan returns an upload URL (pointing to S3) and a set of hidden form fields including a policy and signature.
upscan.demo.howItWorks.step3 = The file is uploaded directly to S3 (either from the user's browser or from the service itself).
upscan.demo.howItWorks.step4 = Upscan verifies the file (virus scan, file type check, size check) and sends an asynchronous callback to the service.
upscan.demo.howItWorks.step5 = The callback contains either a download URL (on success) or failure details. The service updates its state and shows the result to the user.

# User upload page
upscan.userUpload.title = Upload a file
upscan.userUpload.heading = Upload a file
upscan.userUpload.hint = Select a file to upload. It must be smaller than 10MB. Supported formats include PDF, JPG, PNG, and common document types.
upscan.userUpload.submit = Upload file
upscan.userUpload.details.summary = Technical details (for demonstration)
upscan.userUpload.details.reference = Upscan reference: {0}
upscan.userUpload.details.href = Upload URL: {0}
upscan.userUpload.details.explanation = The form below posts directly to the Upscan upload URL (S3 or upscan-stub locally). Hidden fields contain a pre-signed policy and signature. The file never passes through the frontend service.

# Generate and upload page
upscan.generate.title = Enter disclosure details
upscan.generate.heading = Enter disclosure details
upscan.generate.intro = Enter the information below. The service will generate a JSON file from your answers and upload it to Upscan on your behalf.
upscan.generate.fullName.label = Full name
upscan.generate.description.label = Description of disclosure
upscan.generate.description.hint = Provide a brief description of what you are disclosing.
upscan.generate.amount.label = Amount
upscan.generate.amount.hint = Enter the amount in pounds, for example 1500.00
upscan.generate.submit = Generate and upload file
upscan.generate.details.summary = Technical details (for demonstration)
upscan.generate.details.explanation = When you submit this form, the service will: (1) call upscan-initiate to get a pre-signed URL, (2) generate a JSON file from your form data, (3) upload that file to S3 using the pre-signed URL via a server-side multipart POST. The file is then virus-scanned by Upscan and a callback is sent to the service.

